author: ate
msg: Fixing broken test cases because of incomplete spring assembly setup as result of the JS2-634 changes to registry.xml which now requires the page-manager.xml also to be loaded.
As the page-manager.xml depends on the IdGenerator, PageFileCache bean definitions defined in jetspeed-spring.xml and property ${applicationRoot},
I splitted off the IdGenerator and PageFileCache from jetspeed-spring.xml into a new jetspeed-base.xml (ugh, properly naming these becomes troublesome)
and added initializing the ${applicationRoot} property in AbstractSpringTestCase.
All tests are now working again
